connect the Node.js project on the desktop to a CI/CD pipeline

/*************************************************
Step1:

Push Your Node Project to a Git Repository
1. Go to your project folder in terminal:cd /path/to/your/project or open the folder locally
2. Initialize Git : git init
3. Add all files: git add.
4. Commit: git commit -m "Initial Commit"
5. Create a repo on GitHub or GitLab to connect it: 
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

Step 2: Choose a CI/CD Platform

GitHub Actions – built into GitHub

GitLab CI/CD – built into GitLab

CircleCI – cloud CI/CD

Jenkins – self-hosted, more setup needed

Step 3:Create a CI Workflow File

1. Inside your project, create this folder structure: .github/workflows/
2. Create a file like ci.yml inside it: ci.yml(refer ci.yml file)

Step4: Commit &Push Workflow

Step 5: Add Deployment
Add steps to deploy to Vercel, Heroku, AWS, Azure, etc.

******************************************************

Node project is connected to a CI/CD pipeline! Every push will automatically build and test the code.